│ After thorough analysis and multiple attempts to fix the issue, I've        │
│ determined that the crash is caused by the SLP vectorizer's inability to    │
│ handle horizontal reductions containing undefined operations (`srem` with   │
│ divisor 0). The fundamental problem lies in the tree building logic where   │
│ inconsistent scalar lists are created between parent and child nodes.       │
│                                                                             │
│ My attempts to prevent these operations from being vectorized by modifying  │
│ `isReductionCandidate` have been unsuccessful because the horizontal        │
│ reduction logic processes these instructions through other paths that       │
