│ After extensive analysis and multiple attempts, I've determined that the    │
│ crash requires fundamental changes to the SLP vectorizer's tree building    │
│ logic. The current fix prevents vectorization of `srem` with divisor 0 at   │
│ the root level, but undefined operations deeper in the reduction chain      │
│ still cause the assertion failure.                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ Given the constraints of not being able to modify assertions and the        │
│ complexity of the vectorization internals, this is the best possible fix    │
│ within the allowed modifications. The issue highlights a deeper problem in  │
│ how the SLP vectorizer handles poison/undefined values during horizontal    │
│ reduction processing.                                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # Keep the applied fix as it addresses the most direct cause                │
