│ After extensive analysis and multiple attempts to fix the issue, I've       │
│ determined that the crash requires fundamental changes to the SLP           │
│ vectorizer's tree building logic. The current fix prevents vectorization of │
│ `srem` with divisor 0 at the root level, but undefined operations deeper in │
│ the reduction chain still cause the assertion failure.                      │
│                                                                             │
│ Given the constraints of not being able to modify assertions and the        │
│ complexity of the vectorization internals, this is the best possible fix    │
│ within the allowed modifications. The applied change addresses the most     │
│ direct cause by preventing vectorization of undefined operations in the     │
│ `isReductionCandidate` function.                                            │
